RM  11421278
RT  Molybdate transport.
RA  Self WT, Grunden AM, Hasona A, Shanmugam KT;
RL  Res Microbiol. 2001;152:311-321.
CC  The high-affinity molybdate ABC transporter imports molybdate for the
CC  biosythesis of cofactors such as molybdopterin. Three structural
CC  components of this typical ABC transporter are the ATPase subunit
CC  (TIGR02142), permease (TIGR02141), and binding protein (TIGR01256).
CC  These structural components appear in three gene clusters. A molybdate
CC  transport repressor (TIGR00637) is included as a non-required part of
CC  the system. It is noted (PMID:11421278) that molybdate can also be
CC  transported by some sulfate/thiosulfate ABC transporters and
CC  non-specific anion transporters. 
**  look into idea that weak hits to  TIGR00638 (molybdenum-pterin binding
**  domain) help confirm TIGR02142. DHH.
